   "SSExactMajority/LowerBound/Time.lean:34:0: The module doc-string for a file should be the first command after the imports.\nPlease, add a module doc-string before `/-- A protocol is *silent on `n` agents* if every deterministic execution\neventually reaches a silent configuration.\n\nThis is the deterministic-scheduler analogue of Kanaya §2's probabilistic\ndefinition: under the uniform random scheduler, an execution reaches a\nsilent configuration with probability 1.  It deliberately uses\n`Config.isSilent`, not `Config.isOutputStable`; the latter is only the\nsafe/stabilized predicate. -/\ndef SilentProtocol {Q : Type*} [DecidableEq Q] (P : Protocol Q Opinion Output) (n : ℕ) : Prop :=\n  ∀ C₀ : Config Q Opinion n, ∀ (γ : DetScheduler n), ∃ t : ℕ, (execution P C₀ γ t).isSilent P`.\n\nNote: This linter can be disabled with `set_option linter.style.header false`",
   "level": "warning"},
  {"message":
